If the problem of the accused Czech researchers in India, accused of illegal collection of cockroaches, could not be solved, according to the Czech Foreign Minister Karel Schwarzenberg, a certain cooling of the Czech-Indian relations would follow.
The minister declared it today in New York, after meeting with his Indian counterpart Pranab Mukherjee.
