Organizers report an increasing number of bookings
This should be a good winter for German travel agencies:
In terms of bookings for the coming months according to a study, the turnover has increased significantly compared to the previous year - for the winter season, even more than 30 percent.
Despite weak economic prospects, the thirst for travel of Germans remains insatiable according to this study.
With regard to bookings for the winter season, travel agencies recorded a turnover of more than 31 percent compared to the same period the previous year, as the German Federation of Travel Agencies (DRV) reported on Monday in Berlin.
According to the survey of the Research Institute of Markets GfK, increasing numbers of reservations already dominate the autumn months.
Thus the sales figure would have risen to about 11 percent compared to 2007, confided the DRV.
The sources of these results are figures from the GfK, which analyzes monthly booking data from 1,200 travel agencies and makes estimates for the global market.
Travel bookings made since the end of August 2008 would be recorded.
Due to the low dollar price, travel to the US would be particularly in demand, the DRV said.
There, the increase in bookings would amount to about a third.
Besides this, Spain, Turkey and Greece as well as our country would be particularly sought after destinations by the Germans.
Specially organized trips are in high demand, explained the president of the DRV Klaus Laepple.
In view of the rising prices of energy and food products, the costs here would be “more easily calculated for the customer than for an individually organized trip”.
Consumers can save money, among other things, with early booking discounts or All Inclusive offers, Laepple explained.
The summer months have also been very restrained so much so that an increase in sales figures will again be recorded compared to last year - although according to another study, the number of Germans who undertook a trip has decreased compared to the previous year.
